Sentencas: Performance degradation shortens the life of solid oxide fuel cells in practical applications.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Revealing the degradation mechanism is crucial for the continuous improvement of cell durability.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, the effects of cell operating conditions on the terminal voltage and anode microstructure of a Ni-yttria-stabilized zirconia anode-supported single cell were investigated.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructure of the anode active area near the electrolyte was characterized by laser optical microscopy and focused ion beam-scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ni depletion at the anode/electrolyte interface region was observed after 100 h discharge tests.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the long-term stability of the single cell was evaluated at 700 degrees C for 3000 h. After an initial decline, the anode-supported single cell exhibits good durability with a voltage decay rate of 0.72%/kh and an electrode polarization resistance decay rate of 0.17%/kh.
Titulo: Effects of operating conditions on the performance degradation and anode microstructure evolution of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The main performance loss of the cell originates from the initial degradation.
